  "title": "3D Designer (Events & Window Display)",
  "description": "<p>We‚Äôre looking for a 3D Designer with a strong sense of design and technical know-how to bring events, window displays, and brand activations to life. You should have hands-on experience in event production, be familiar with materials and fabrication techniques, and be confident in producing technical drawings for build and installation.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Design 3D concepts for events, window displays, and installations</li><li>Produce accurate technical drawings and build specifications</li><li>Develop mood boards, sketches, and high-quality renderings</li><li>Work closely with internal teams, fabricators, and production crews</li><li>Translate brand concepts into immersive spatial experiences</li><li>Refine designs to suit budgets, site constraints, and production feasibility</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Interior, Exhibition, or Spatial Design</li><li><strong>Proficiency in SketchUp is a must.</strong></li><li>Proficiency in V-Ray, AutoCAD or similar tools</li><li>Minimum 3 years of experience in event production or a related field</li><li>Strong understanding of materials, fabrication methods, and installation processes</li><li>Skilled in Adobe Creative Suite for layout and presentation</li><li>Ability to manage multiple projects under tight deadlines</li></ul><p><strong>Bonus</strong></p><ul><li>Experience with luxury, retail, or experiential brand activations</li><li>Familiarity with on-site setup and safety protocols</li></ul>",
